This utility is used to pack small objects into a large object.  It 
works only on the namespace provided by the user.  The
GPFS Programming Interface is used to perform an inode scan 
in order to obtain xattr information about the objects.

Install:
make

Usage: marfs_packer -d gpfs_path -n namespace [-l] [-h]

-d gpfs_path  

   Mount path for the targeted gpfs file system.

-n namespace       

   The namespace targeted for packing.

-l

   list a summary of objects counts that can be 
   packed without actually packing 

-h

   provides script usage information
